
===================================
📌 1. Finglish Version (Persian Latin Script)
===================================

📖 **Tashrih:**
    Dastoor `autoreconf` baraye sakhtan ya update kardan file-haye configure script (mesle `configure`) dar project-haye software estefade mishavad. In kar be developer-ha komak mikonad ke project-haye khod ra rooye system-haye mokhtalef compile va install konand.

⚙️ **Gozine-ha:**
    🔹 `autoreconf -i`  --> 📦 Copy kardan file-haye supporti agar mojood nabashand.
    🔹 `autoreconf -f`  --> 🔄 Force kardan update hata agar file-ha tagheer nakarde bashand.
    🔹 `autoreconf -v`  --> 🗣️ Namayesh dadan etela'at bishtar dar morede chigoonegi kar kardan dastoor.
    🔹 `autoreconf -s`  --> 🤫 Silent mode, yani kamtar etela'at chap shavad.

🛠 **Mesal-ha:**

    $ autoreconf
    
    🔹 Sakhtan ya update kardan configure script ba estefade az file-haye `configure.ac` ya `configure.in`.

    $ autoreconf -i
    
    🔹 Copy kardan file-haye lazem agar mojood nabashand va update kardan configure script.

✅ **Mesal sade:**

    $ autoreconf -fiv
    
    🔹 Force kardan update, copy kardan file-haye supporti agar nabashand, va namayesh dadan etela'at bishtar dar morede chigoonegi kar kardan dastoor.

===================================
📌 2. English Version
===================================

📖 **Description:**
    The `autoreconf` command is used to generate or update the configuration scripts (like `configure`) for software projects.  This helps developers compile and install their projects on various systems.

⚙️ **Options:**
    🔹 `autoreconf -i`  --> 📦 Copy missing support files, if they don't exist.
    🔹 `autoreconf -f`  --> 🔄 Force an update even if files haven't changed.
    🔹 `autoreconf -v`  --> 🗣️ Verbose mode, showing more information about how the command works.
    🔹 `autoreconf -s`  --> 🤫 Silent mode, reducing the amount of output.

🛠 **Examples:**

    $ autoreconf
    
    🔹 Generate or update the configuration scripts using `configure.ac` or `configure.in` files.

    $ autoreconf -i
    
    🔹 Copy necessary support files if they are missing and update the configuration scripts.

✅ **Simple Example:**

    $ autoreconf -fiv
    
    🔹 Force an update, copy missing support files, and provide verbose output about the command's operation.

